sz81
------------------------------------------
sz81 is a Sinclair ZX80/ZX81 emulator very much based upon the work of Ian
Collier's xz80 and Russell Marks's z81 but employing the highly portable SDL
and including additional functionality and features for desktop computers and
portable devices.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.11.2-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sz81.sourceforge.io/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/sz81/sz81-2.1.7-source.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack sz81-2.1.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./sz81-2.1.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sz81-2.1.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/sz81-2.1.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(sz81)
  /usr/bin/sz81.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sz81.README
